Source.Contents:
/#
   Specifies the notional of return type swap. When used in the equity leg, the definition will typically combine the actual amount (using the notional component defined by the FpML industry group) and the determination method. When used in the interest leg, the definition will typically point to the definition of the equity leg.
 #/
record FpML5.transparency.ReturnSwapNotional {
  # A reference to the return swap notional amount defined elsewhere in this document.
  relativeNotionalAmount : FpML5.transparency.ReturnSwapNotionalAmountReference

  # A reference to the return swap notional determination method defined elsewhere in this document.
  relativeDeterminationMethod : FpML5.transparency.DeterminationMethodReference

  # Specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined.
  determinationMethod : string

  # The notional amount.
  notionalAmount : FpML5.transparency.NotionalAmount

  id : string?

}

relativeNotionalAmount.Doc: A reference to the return swap notional amount defined elsewhere in this document.
relativeNotionalAmount.Name: relativeNotionalAmount

relativeDeterminationMethod.Doc: A reference to the return swap notional determination method defined elsewhere in this document.
relativeDeterminationMethod.Name: relativeDeterminationMethod

determinationMethod.Doc: Specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined.
determinationMethod.Name: determinationMethod
